                    <sex value="M" source="#bib1258-1">male</sex>
                    <death when="0322" syriaca-computed-start="0322-01-01" source="#bib1258-1">0322</death>
                    <note>Fiey provides the following bibliographic citations: <quote source="#bib1258-1">Le martyrologe de Rabban $a1Iba fete un I:Jabib, non identifie, au 11 mars.
1MS, I, 144- 60; Burkitt, Euphemia, 26*-43* , 112- 28; BHO, 367.
Suhada ', I, 102- 12.
Homelie metrique de Jacques de Sarug: AMS, I, 160- 72 ; BHO, 368.
Vies des saints, XI, 15 novembre, 472-75, avec references.
Segal, Edessa, 85- 86.
BS, I, 77- 81 (G.M. Fusconi/S. Orienti).</quote>
                    </note>
                    <note type="abstract">Habib was a deacon of the village of Telshaha near Edessa. He continued, despite the persecution that caused the death of <persName ref=" http://syriaca.org/person/1257">Shmona and Guria</persName>, to travel from village to village encouraging the Christians. It was in the region of Zeugma on the Euphrates when he learned that Lysanius was looking for him. He was imprisoned and burnt to death, and his mother accompanied him to his death. He was entombed near Shmona and Guria.</note>
                    <note type="disambiguation">with Shmona and Guria</note>
                    <note type="disambiguation">edessan martyr</note>
                    <event type="attestation" xml:id="attestation1258-1" source="#bib1258-1">
